result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 16CM-128 and 16CM-190 with companion citations - Both Cases Called @ 3:45 PM: Defendant Pedro Hernandez-Hernandez in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Enrique Soria present as Interpreter.  Oath administered at previous hearing today.  16CM-128 and 16CM-190:  Both Complaints  Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  ADA serves add'l copies of Complaints - Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def does not wish counsel today and is prepared to resolve the matters.  In light of pleas expected, the State will move to dismiss 16CM-128 and 16TR-866.    Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. 16CM-190 (OAR) Plea: NC   16TR-867 (OWI) Plea: NC    Court accepts pleas and enters JOC.   Upon motion of the State - 16CM-128 and 16TR-868 both DRI.  ADA argues as to OWI - a guideline penalty for .11 PBT.   16CM190 - 10 days WCJ.  Statement by Def:  None offered.  The Court:  16CM-190 - 10 days WCJ, Report 7/1/2016, Huber, no TS credit, GT credit, Court Costs plus  DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.  16TR-867:  9 mos DL Rev, Forfeiture of $811.50; No IID requirement.  16CM-128 to be applied against the financial obligations in 16CM-190 and 16TR-867.  Hispanic Appeal Rights Given.
